name: ClothingWornDuringMeasureReferenceSet
title: Clothing worn during measure reference set
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Clothing worn during measure value set as defined by the Clinical Information Modeling Initiative.),(Data Element Scope: This reference set contains concepts used to result the amount of clothing worn during the measure, referencing the SNOMED Code 248159006 "State of dress (observable entity)" and the LOINC "Clothing worn during measure" 8352-7, resulting the SNOMED CT concept: Clothing worn during measure reference set (foundation metadata concept) 941000205105.),(Inclusion Criteria: This value set is missing 2 concepts from the HSPC extension namespace: Wearing street clothes with shoes (finding) 971000205103, Wearing street clothes, no shoes (finding) 961000205106.),(Exclusion Criteria: )
